Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.93,0:00:03.85,sign_23_2_Sakaguchi_Ango,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaguchi Ango
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.31,0:00:03.30,Stray Dogs - Italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaguchi Ango.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.15,0:00:11.24,sign_196_4_A_Mysterious_Int,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,A Mysterious Intellectual...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.19,0:00:11.23,Stray Dogs - Italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,A mysterious intellectual...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.31,0:00:15.40,Stray Dogs - Italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.28,0:00:19.37,sign_391_7_No_One_Knew_Who_,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,No One Knew Who You Really Were
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.36,0:00:19.04,Stray Dogs - Italics,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,No one knew who you really were.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.37,0:00:22.54,sign_465_8_Western_style_Fo,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Western-style Food\N and Curry\N\NFreedom
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.54,0:00:25.04,sign_541_9_Freedom,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.54,0:00:32.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Shop,0000,0000,0000,,How's the curry taste?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.17,0:00:34.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The same as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.87,0:00:37.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Gy,0000,0000,0000,,How are the kids doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.81,0:00:40.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Shop,0000,0000,0000,,The same as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.75,0:00:43.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Shop,0000,0000,0000,,They're all upstairs,\N so why don't you go say hi?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.47,0:01:07.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's me. I'm coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.95,0:01:11.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,How are you guys doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.04,0:01:17.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're not causing the old man\N any trouble, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.60,0:01:22.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Kosu,0000,0000,0000,,I've got you now!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.30,0:01:23.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Hup!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.39,0:01:32.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Kosu,0000,0000,0000,,How's that, Odasaku? You give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.19,0:01:37.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently I'm going to have to show you \Njust how scary the real mafia is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.70,0:03:07.70,Stray Dogs - Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{op}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.26,0:03:09.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,You give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.83,0:03:10.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Kosu,0000,0000,0000,,Nope!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.24,0:03:12.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.66,0:03:15.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have some Port Mafia-style torture.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.28,0:03:21.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Kosu,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! I'll die! I'll die!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.41,0:03:26.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Kosu,0000,0000,0000,,No! Stop! Seriously, stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.18,0:03:32.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Kosu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll definitely get you next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.29,0:03:35.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I'll look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.69,0:03:38.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Hot! This is too hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:41.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Did you add lava as the secret \Ningredient or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.39,0:03:44.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku-chan eats that all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.67,0:03:46.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,How were the kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.98,0:03:48.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,The same as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.74,0:03:50.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Are those all the kids \Nthat lost their parents in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.66,0:03:52.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,the Ryuuzu Dispute two years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.75,0:03:54.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You're Oda Sakunosuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:56.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,A member of the mafia who never kills,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.00,0:03:57.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,you have no interest in moving up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.82,0:03:59.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,and you take care of orphans.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.58,0:04:01.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You sure are strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.32,0:04:04.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You're the strangest person \Nin the Port Mafia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.38,0:04:06.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Not as strange as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.00,0:04:10.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Here are the living expenses for \Nthose kids for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.56,0:04:14.64,Stray Dogs - Default,Shop,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure? I don't mind pitching in...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.80,0:04:18.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I'm already grateful that you're \Ngiving them a place to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.69,0:04:20.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,And as long as I get to eat the \Ncurry here whenever I want,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.46,0:04:24.65,Stray Dogs - Top,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Hot... So hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:22.53,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.87,0:04:24.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,And you came here today \Nconcerning that thing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.77,0:04:27.53,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.91,0:04:30.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I've come to the conclusion
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.87,0:04:33.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,that they are an organization\N of gifted members from overseas.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.67,0:04:36.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,They were being chased by a \Ngifted agency from England
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.54,0:04:38.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,called the Order of the Clock Tower,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.99,0:04:41.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,and came scurrying from Europe to Japan...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.02,0:04:46.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,And what did those guys come \Nall the way to Japan for?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.05,0:04:48.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,They escaped to a foreign land...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.72,0:04:51.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,So maybe something was already here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.81,0:04:56.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,That's possible... But there's one \Nthing that bugs me about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.35,0:04:58.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You want to say that the soldiers \Nwere far too skilled, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.12,0:05:00.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.26,0:05:02.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,They're former soldiers...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.82,0:05:04.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,According to my information,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.28,0:05:05.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,the head of that organization
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.86,0:05:09.53,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,uses a powerful gift \Nto command veteran soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.24,0:05:12.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Powerful gift?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.90,0:05:15.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Does the boss know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.63,0:05:17.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I reported it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.03,0:05:22.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Then he ordered me to come up with an \Nanti-Mimic strategy and command the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.14,0:05:25.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I already set up various traps.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.07,0:05:30.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to ask you something \Nrather rudimentary,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.25,0:05:32.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,but if it's an international criminal \Norganization with gifted members,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.81,0:05:35.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't this be a matter for the government agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.02,0:05:39.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Da,0000,0000,0000,,Are you referring to the Ministry of Home Affairs'\N Supernatural Special Operations Division?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.43,0:05:42.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,They won't show up unless the \Nsituation is rather extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.23,0:05:45.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Because to the outside world, \Nthey technically don't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.75,0:05:47.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,And what about Ango?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:50.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,It's basically been confirmed that Ango
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.57,0:05:53.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,was the one who leaked the \Npasscode on the storage unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.07,0:05:58.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Did Ango betray the organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.24,0:06:02.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Everything makes perfect \Nsense if we believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.08,0:06:11.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.37,0:06:14.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.25,0:06:20.60,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,A mouse fell into one of my traps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.60,0:06:23.61,sign_9126_87_Episode_14__Nowh,Title,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 14: Nowhere to Return
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.30,0:06:36.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Ponc,0000,0000,0000,,Just like our information said.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.29,0:06:39.16,sign_9550_90_Unlocked,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Unlocked
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.00,0:06:42.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Ponc,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.83,0:06:52.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Ponc,0000,0000,0000,,Sleeping gas... So this was a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.43,0:07:06.22,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,This is an accounting facility that the \NPort Mafia uses for money laundering.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.87,0:07:10.86,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Three years ago, Sakaguchi Ango \Nwas scouted by the Port Mafia,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.86,0:07:12.95,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,and worked here for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.61,0:07:16.23,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,There are records of Ango here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.26,0:07:20.64,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm going to get to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.06,0:07:22.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't mind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.84,0:07:25.33,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,This is a great place to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.89,0:07:28.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll ask to be transferred here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.38,0:07:30.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Every youngster that's ever said that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.47,0:07:34.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,usually goes running out of \Nhere in less than three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.53,0:07:36.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's too boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.06,0:07:38.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Please, take your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.85,0:07:47.78,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I found some information that bothered me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.79,0:07:52.50,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago, Ango went to \NEurope on a business trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.91,0:07:57.89,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,The purpose was to negotiate a deal \Nwith a local stolen car broker.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.53,0:07:59.57,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,That must be when
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.99,0:08:03.07,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,he agreed to become a \Ndouble agent for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.73,0:08:10.09,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,This was the place where \NDazai and I first met Ango.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.38,0:08:15.80,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind not coming any closer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.01,0:08:17.01,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,You smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.29,0:08:20.50,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Two years ago, during the Ryuuzu Dispute,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:23.23,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai and I got orders from above
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.23,0:08:25.73,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,and were put in charge of taking \Ncare of the corpses
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.73,0:08:27.94,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,of organization members \Nwho had died in the dispute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.75,0:08:28.32,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Do I smell...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.32,0:08:31.14,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Mostly, it was to bring \Nback their belongings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.69,0:08:34.15,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,If the police were to get \Ntheir hands on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.15,0:08:36.70,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,they could be used as evidence for \Nthe organized crime prevention law
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.70,0:08:38.28,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,and it would be rather troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.13,0:08:40.93,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You must be new.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.86,0:08:43.42,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,State your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.76,0:08:45.56,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,It's Sakaguchi Ango.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.56,0:08:46.68,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Ango-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.68,0:08:48.66,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You are truly amusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.45,0:08:50.08,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,You reek!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.28,0:08:53.75,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure the boss isn't going \Nto like you doing things like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.06,0:08:57.26,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to say that \Nyou know what I'm doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.37,0:09:00.30,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You're making a life record \Nof those who died.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.30,0:09:01.38,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.52,0:09:04.51,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,A life record of those who died?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.52,0:09:06.19,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,These three died in the incident
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.19,0:09:09.32,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,that happened last night where \Nexecutives were attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.63,0:09:13.79,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Umeki Kurehito, Saegusa Shoukichi, \NIshige Miroku.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.19,0:09:15.86,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Umeki was a former MP.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.86,0:09:18.37,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,He was dishonorably discharged \Nfor killing a coworker.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.37,0:09:19.98,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Both of his parents had died.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.41,0:09:24.27,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You're recording the dead's history \Nand family information, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.50,0:09:26.45,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,The death of a person is \Nnot just some number.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.83,0:09:29.75,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Every one of their lives \Nmust have some meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.71,0:09:33.76,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,What's written here is something \Nyou could never feel
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:35.92,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,from just the words, "three dead."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.11,0:09:37.88,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,It's their breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.18,0:09:39.88,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,What did the boss say about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.17,0:09:45.40,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I forced all 84 people who have died \Nso far in the dispute upon him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.77,0:09:47.56,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,At first, he hated it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.56,0:09:49.36,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,but now he says it's valuable information
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.36,0:09:50.99,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,to get to know everything \Nabout the organization
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.99,0:09:52.42,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,and was rather pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.42,0:09:54.72,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daz,0000,0000,0000,,See? Isn't he amusing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.72,0:09:58.36,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of circumstances cause one to \Nthink up such a unique job as this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.74,0:10:00.74,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,There's one way to find out...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.95,0:10:03.83,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,We just need to take him to \Nour usual place after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.85,0:10:05.94,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daz,0000,0000,0000,,That's a brilliant idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.05,0:10:07.19,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.19,0:10:09.15,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I have other work I need to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.19,0:10:11.49,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Dz,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Odasaku! There's one way to free him up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.68,0:10:13.76,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,If we hug him as hard as we can,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.76,0:10:16.71,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,he won't be able to work anymore \Nfrom the smell and the filth!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.71,0:10:17.92,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.71,0:10:19.95,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.93,0:10:22.30,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ago,0000,0000,0000,,This is my best suit! Stop this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.30,0:10:24.81,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ago,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to get angry! \NI'm seriously going to get angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.13,0:10:55.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like an explanation...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.55,0:10:58.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We captured Mimic's vanguard \Nthat attacked the casino
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.30,0:11:01.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,with the knockout gas as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.68,0:11:06.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,One of them committed suicide, \Nbut we brought the other three here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:09.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We were planning to have them \Ntalk about the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.22,0:11:12.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We even removed the poison \Nhidden in their teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.97,0:11:14.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.92,0:11:17.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Because this was all part of my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:19.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,What I want to know is what \Nhappened after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.42,0:11:23.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,O-One of the soldiers woke up \Nearlier than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.97,0:11:25.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Before we could get handcuffs on him,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.42,0:11:27.33,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,he stole one of our guns
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.33,0:11:30.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,and most likely shot his comrades \Nso they couldn't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.73,0:11:32.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He also came after us...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.29,0:11:36.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Aku,0000,0000,0000,,So I decided to take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.14,0:11:48.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Aku,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.49,0:11:51.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.06,0:11:54.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.94,0:11:57.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You defeated the fearsome, unyielding enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.90,0:12:00.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,and protected our comrades, Akutagawa-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.24,0:12:03.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,That's absolutely splendid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.77,0:12:05.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,If it weren't for your powers,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.62,0:12:07.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,they wouldn't have been able to defeat
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.62,0:12:10.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,such a powerful enemy on \Ntheir own in a single blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.84,0:12:13.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing less from my subordinate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.27,0:12:17.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you, all of the \Nenemies we captured are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.00,0:12:21.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,The soldiers that I worked so hard to \Nlay a trap for just to keep alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.48,0:12:24.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Now our clues are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.14,0:12:29.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,If even one of them were alive, we could \Nhave found out their headquarters, motive,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.34,0:12:31.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,their commander's lineage, name,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.87,0:12:34.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,and the powers they use \Nto command the organization...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.78,0:12:37.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,We could have gotten all of \Nthat important information.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.39,0:12:39.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Aku,0000,0000,0000,,Information?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.11,0:12:41.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Aku,0000,0000,0000,,As if I would—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.05,0:12:51.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,To you, it must have seemed like I was \Nwaiting to hear some excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.72,0:12:53.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for giving you the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.45,0:12:56.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Hand me your gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.02,0:13:03.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Someone I know happens to be \Ntaking care of some orphans...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.74,0:13:06.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,If Odasaku happened to pick \Nyou up from the slums,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.96,0:13:09.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that he wouldn't \Nhave abandoned you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.02,0:13:11.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,He would have patiently \Nand firmly guided you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.72,0:13:13.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,That's what righteousness is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:18.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,However, I'm a man hated by righteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.88,0:13:20.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Men like me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.64,0:13:23.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Do this to their useless subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.07,0:13:33.36,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.16,0:13:37.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,See? You can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.24,0:13:42.33,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,How many times have I told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.31,0:13:47.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Cutting open unfortunate hostages\N isn't the only thing you're good for.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.67,0:13:50.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You should be able to use your \Npowers for defense, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.89,0:13:54.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Aku,0000,0000,0000,,I've never been able to successfully \Ndo that before this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.14,0:13:56.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,But you just did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.63,0:13:58.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that great?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.36,0:14:01.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,The next time you mess up...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.16,0:14:04.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I'll punch you twice, \Nand shoot you five times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.13,0:14:06.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.62,0:14:09.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.18,0:14:13.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Let's check their corpses. \NSomething might turn up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.65,0:14:16.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Um... What should we check on the corpses?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.16,0:14:17.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.00,0:14:20.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to find any trace \Nof their hideout that we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.83,0:14:23.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,The soles of their shoes, their pocket lint,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.06,0:14:24.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,anything sticking to their clothes...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.48,0:14:26.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,All of those are clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.34,0:14:27.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,For crying out loud...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.84,0:14:30.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently all of my subordinates \Nmust think that beating our enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.14,0:14:32.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,to death is the only thing the mafia does.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.44,0:14:36.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, Odasaku might figure \Nthis all out on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.51,0:14:39.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I know that man, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.27,0:14:43.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Though he is part of the mafia, \Nhe lacks the guts to kill a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.81,0:14:47.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see him associating \Nwith you at all, Dazai-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.85,0:14:49.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You've made two mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.78,0:14:54.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Guts have nothing to do with being able \Nto associate with someone or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.80,0:14:56.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,The other is a warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.29,0:14:59.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,You'd be better off not angering Odasaku...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.43,0:15:01.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.05,0:15:04.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,If he were to truly become angry \Nfrom the bottom of his heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.59,0:15:06.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,everyone in this room
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.76,0:15:09.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,would be dead before any of \Nus could draw our guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.38,0:15:11.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,When Odasaku isn't holding back,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.05,0:15:13.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,he's more terrifying than \Nany Port Mafia member.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.71,0:15:18.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Akutagawa-kun, you could never defeat \NOdasaku in a hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.20,0:15:20.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Aku,0000,0000,0000,,No... That's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.47,0:15:22.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Aku,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai-san, who do you think—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.31,0:15:23.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,All right, back to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.36,0:15:28.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,I know the enemy's trouble, but we need \Nto hurry up and take care of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.42,0:15:32.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Or the Supernatural Special Operations Division\N will show up and cause even more trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.70,0:15:46.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,This is Oda.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.84,0:15:49.93,Stray Dogs - Italics,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Odasaku. I found a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.21,0:15:52.71,Stray Dogs - Italics,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Would you head over to the \Nplace I'm about to tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.90,0:15:54.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,You discovered the enemy's hideout?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.09,0:15:56.13,Stray Dogs - Italics,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.54,0:15:57.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Did their soldiers tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.07,0:15:58.95,Stray Dogs - Italics,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Nope...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.68,0:16:01.85,Stray Dogs - Italics,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,But we were able to get \Nresults from a dried leaf
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:03.75,Stray Dogs - Italics,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,that was stuck to the bottom \Nof one of their shoes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.30,0:16:05.33,Stray Dogs - Italics,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,It was indeed a leaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.00,0:16:14.48,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,The one who betrayed the \Norganization, Sakaguchi Ango...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.83,0:16:17.30,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,His information must be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.50,0:16:23.85,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai's subordinates should \Nbe getting here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.15,0:16:27.34,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to check out the \Nfacility before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.00,0:16:32.13,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Because I had a hunch...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.19,0:16:37.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.45,0:16:38.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.38,0:16:41.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.21,0:16:43.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,This was the facility the enemy \Nwas using as their hideout!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.71,0:16:46.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you might have needed some help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.73,0:16:48.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't need any help!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.22,0:16:49.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.13,0:16:53.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Let me deduce one of the reasons \Nthat you're troubled right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.53,0:16:57.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Mimic found out that you were a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.74,0:16:58.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.77,0:17:03.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone in the Port Mafia believes \N you're a spy for Mimic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.36,0:17:04.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,But it's the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.46,0:17:09.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaguchi Ango is a Port Mafia \Nspy that infiltrated Mimic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.19,0:17:13.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,The reason those guys were looking \Ninto your room with a sniper's scope
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.06,0:17:17.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,was so that the Graugeist, hidden \Nin your room, wouldn't be stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.21,0:17:23.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,But why didn't they hurry up and \Nsnipe the boss of the Port Mafia?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.65,0:17:28.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,That's because you lied, and said you \Ndidn't know where the boss was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.14,0:17:34.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,The reason you did that, as well as \Neverything you said or didn't say,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.11,0:17:36.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,were all determined by the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.60,0:17:39.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku-san, please run...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.59,0:17:43.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I, of all people, messed up...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.42,0:17:47.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,There are time bombs hidden \Nthroughout this building...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.17,0:17:51.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,They were planning to burn me to death \Nfor being the traitor that I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.02,0:17:51.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.10,0:17:54.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,You were asking for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.92,0:18:00.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Ango!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.16,0:18:02.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,How much longer until the bombs go off?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.36,0:18:05.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you'd be able to tell \Nwith your powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:08.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Like my gift is that convenient...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.68,0:18:10.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.81,0:18:12.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we still \Nhave a few seconds left!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.50,0:18:24.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.37,0:18:32.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.17,0:18:33.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.72,0:18:45.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.29,0:18:49.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not cut out for all this adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.18,0:18:52.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,But... You saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.33,0:18:55.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Da,0000,0000,0000,,How much does our boss know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.09,0:18:57.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Nearly everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.32,0:19:01.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who knew about me \Ninfiltrating Mimic was the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.29,0:19:06.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,So the reason the boss had me \Nlook for you was for insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.42,0:19:11.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Because he knew that I would look for you, \Neven if I didn't know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.31,0:19:13.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I have to report to him immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.36,0:19:15.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,The head of Mimic is an \Nextremely dangerous man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.73,0:19:18.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,He plans to crush the Port Mafia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.13,0:19:19.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,What's the head's name?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.65,0:19:22.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,His name is Gide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.13,0:19:24.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,He has a very powerful gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.26,0:19:27.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,We mustn't fight him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.74,0:19:30.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku-san, especially you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.72,0:19:35.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,The gun that was in that lockbox, \Nthe Graugeist, is a sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.47,0:19:38.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,There is a special carving \Nin the cocking piece,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.95,0:19:42.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,and that proves that you \Nare a member of Mimic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.33,0:19:44.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is Mimic, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.91,0:19:47.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,They are the remnants of \Nthose defeated in the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.49,0:19:49.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,that can only survive on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.85,0:19:54.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,They are all still haunted by the war...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.83,0:19:58.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,What's that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.42,0:20:08.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,A ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.89,0:20:24.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.31,0:20:29.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,It's poison...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.58,0:20:33.28,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,My ability, Flawless,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.28,0:20:35.77,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,allows me to see a few \Nseconds into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.43,0:20:40.08,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,But in the cases where I've realized \Nthe danger in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.08,0:20:42.36,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,after already falling for the trap,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.36,0:20:43.95,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,I can't avoid it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.32,0:20:48.39,Stray Dogs - Italics,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,The person who set up this \Ntrap knew about my powers...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.82,0:20:54.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Ango... Run...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.70,0:20:55.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Odasaku-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.65,0:21:02.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Everything that I just told \Nyou about Mimic is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.99,0:21:04.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,It is not a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.14,0:21:09.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for saving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.81,0:21:10.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.29,0:21:15.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,If it were possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.08,0:21:20.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,I would have loved to go drinking \Nwith you and Dazai-kun again
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.64,0:21:22.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,at the usual place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.85,0:21:36.77,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,There are those who actually think
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.77,0:21:41.28,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,that powers can \Nbe a tool to seduce women.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.28,0:21:46.53,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,But we couldn't use our abilities to \Nseduce women, even if we wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.79,0:21:50.22,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we tried, they'd think \Nwe're creepy and we'd fuzz up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.75,0:21:51.81,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Ango,0000,0000,0000,,"Fuzz up"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.99,0:21:54.83,Stray Dogs - Flashback,Daza,0000,0000,0000,,Yup. Fuzz up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.11,0:22:03.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Dazai...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.17,0:22:08.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Oda,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I fuzzed up...
